The public leaderboard¶

show_leaderboard[source]

show_leaderboard(fname:Union[str, Path], score_bounds:tuple=None, col:str='Score', scale:str='linear', score_ascending:bool=True, bins:int=50, user_score:float=None, user:str='my')

Shows top competitors using display_all and shows the score distribution.

One way to gauge where the model score lies on the public leader board relative to other submissions is to manually go through the list. But since Kaggle is so nice and directly provide a download button in the public leaderboard tab we can just download it as done above and visualize it with show_leaderboard and display_all.

The red dot marks the location of your model score. The title gives you an estimate in which percentile you are. By default the scores are sorted in ascending order. In the example below a score of 0.1 is among the top 1.11% scores. A larger score value would result in a larger %.

show_leaderboard(fname_leaderboard, score_bounds=(None, 1.25), bins=100, user="fastai course", user_score=.1)
